UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2281
1 AN ACT relating to the rights of tenants.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 383 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) As used in this section:
6 (a) "Family member" means an owner's father, mother, brother, sister, spouse,
7 son, daughter, stepson, stepdaughter, grandchild, aunt, uncle, son-in-law,
8 or daughter-in-law;
9 (b) "Material terms" means essential terms for the sale of residential real
10 property that are commercially reasonable, made in good faith, and adhere
11 to generally accepted residential real estate practices, and:
12 1. Include the sale price, settlement date, and other contingencies; and
13 2. Shall not include restrictions on financing methods or the right of
14 inspection;
15 (c) "Owner" means a person, association, corporation, partnership, or other
16 entity having title to a residential rental property;
17 (d) "Residential rental property" means a tenant-occupied rental property for
18 residential use with three (3) or fewer individual dwelling units;
19 (e) "Sale" means the sale and transfer of title of a residential rental property by
20 an owner to a third-party purchaser, but does not include a transfer of title:
21 1. From an owner to a:
22 a. Family member;
23 b. Business entity wholly owned by the owner;
24 c. Local government or the Commonwealth;
25 d. Revocable trust, without actual consideration of the transfer,
26 where the owner is the beneficiary of the trust; or
27 e. Nonprofit organization exempt from taxation under Section
Page 1 of 4
